< Date>
1611249494797</Date>
< Rating>
5<//Rating>
<review>Our stay at Golden Shores RV resort was beautiful. Our spot was able to accommodate our small car and truck. The resort backs up to a bike/running path with easy access to downtown Long Beach. The sunsets here are amazing. There even is a dog park with turf for dogs to run around in. People in the park seem joyous and happy. Showers and bathrooms are kept neat and clean. The laundry room has 5 washers and dryers. The pool/sauna area is large enough for a few families to enjoy together. The front is gated, and the lease/manager lives on property.
Parking is limited and passes are not given regularly. If you have an extra vehicle, be prepared to store or park it elsewhere.
Lock up EVERYTHING. If you have a bike, make sure you have a lock that cannot be cut. Because the trail backs up to the park, a lot of homeless and thieves walk the trail at night. Bikes have been stolen even when chained up. Police will not do anything. If the crime was not caught on camera, they do not care. Including locking your bike you would also be wise to lock your vehicles and bins on your campers. The park has security that makes their rounds at night.
Overall, the park is very well kept. The flowers blooming are a beautiful site! Employees are kind and helpful. We did enjoy our stay and possibly would consider returning.</review><Pictures>None</Pictures>< resp>
{'time': 1611251311516, 'text': 'Thanks so much for taking the time to share this feedback. We are happy to hear you had a great experience at Golden Shore RV Park. We hope see you again!!!'}<//resp>

<name>Ryan Jones< /name><Review>My wife and I stayed at Golden Shore RV Resort from May of this year until today. We are both travel nurses and are in Southern California on assignment. Our stay here has been phenomenal. The area is beautiful, the weather is fantastic, the bike path is amazing, and the staff are very friendly and accommodating. The bathrooms and showers are immaculate. We felt very safe taking 5+ mile walks at night. I couldn't recommend Golden Shore enough. Stayed in a back-in site with my 28ft trailer. Great location. Facilities are well kept. Expensive - more so during major events, as you might expect. <user>100981977859806277358< /user>< user_name>

< Time>
1490240610209< /Time>
<Rating>4</Rating>< Review>
This is our 2nd stay at the conveniently located park in downtown Long Beach.   We stayed for 3 nights total.

Pros:
-Close to major attractions including the Aquarium, Catalina Ferry, Queen Mary, & Rainbow Harbor.
-Close to a good variety of restaurants to choose from.
-Pool and Spa is a big plus for the kids.
-Staff was friendly and helpful.
-The park is secured by a gate which requires a code to access.

Cons:
-WiFi access is works 25% of the time and it is not free.
-Very close to street traffic which is also noticeable at night.
-No awnings or any sort of tent covering allowed which is unheard of.< /Review>

<text>Close to most of the "Long Beach To Do" list. The Aquarium of the Pacific, The Pike, Pierpoint Marina, and tons of shopping and restaurants like and Yard House are within walking distance. So location is pretty good for an RV park.

On the other hand the placement of this RV park is not the greatest. It's adjacent to the last exit on the 710 Freeway; bordered on the north by several 12-story office buildings; and bordered on the south by a mosquito estuary (j/k).

Price is fair for what you get. Clean (mostly level) sites, pool, spa, bathrooms, showers, laundry, full hookups including cable, a little general store. Several maintenance & security on the grounds throughout the day and night. The place is entirely chain link fenced in plus barbed wire so we felt pretty safe! üòÖ

We only stayed one night but we'd come back again for a couple of days.<//text>< pics>

This place has beautiful views and lots of nice, grassy areas! It‚Äôs also central to a lot of awesome LA spots. The maintenance is wonderful‚Äî very clean facility!

They said it was due to people stealing toilet paper (not sure what that has to do with customers now, especially since it‚Äôs now easily accessible at any store). I know there should be Covid-19 changes at each place, but I don‚Äôt know how you expect people to just not use the bathroom for 12 hours.

We also called several times about availability and they said they were sold out for the week. Called the next day and they magically had several spots open and even vacancies through the night, no reservation needed. The tone of the staff in front was not kind by any means.

< Text>
Clean park. Friendly staff. Sites might be a bit small but certainly adequate.  Restrooms and showers are clean, well lit and available 24 hours a day.  Conveniently located near downtown Long Beach,  Shoreline Village, Catalina Express, walking and biking trail and restaurants.  All within a 20 minute walk.< /Text>

< Text>
My husband and I stayed here in Aug 2019. If our trip was specifically to hang out as a couple, we would have had a great stay, and likely this rating would have been 5 out of 5 stars for everything.  Our goal was to have friends and family visit sporadically throughout the weekend, and we found out quickly that this is NOT the place for us if we intended to have visitors.  Parking is a problem EVERYWHERE in Long Beach, and this place is no exception. The problem comes in when they block off visitor parking with cones, restrict it to one car, two hours per site PER DAY, despite  the fact there are several empty spots. They won‚Äôt work with you at all. My family member got a two hour pass while waiting for a parking spot in the few metered spots out front to become available. One was available quickly, so he moved his car. We took the pass back in the office and asked for a different pass so another family member could utilize the two hour parking until another site opened up. That‚Äôs when we learned about the limit of one two hour pass per site per day. It‚Äôs really ridiculous.
We had a visitor come visit for an hour when the office was closed. We tried to call to find out how to get them in, but it went to vm. We just had them park for an hour, and when we came out, a worker had already ticketed their car and said they were about to call a tow truck. Not a very welcome greeting!!
The manager was the only one who helped at all. She recommended places to park, but nothing was a decent option.
This place is all about the R&R, and I‚Äôm not referring to rest and relaxation. Read those rules and regulations!!! I suggested an addition to the R&R that might be helpful to people (instead of ‚Äúdon‚Äôt do this and don‚Äôt do that‚Äù) and they had no desire to even consider my suggestion.
I have not experienced what they experience, but I just feel like there‚Äôs got to be a kinder way to handle things and talk to people.
Bottom line, it was an overall frustrating trip with regard to dealing with the staff. We will find another place to stay so we can have visitors when we‚Äôre in California.<//Text>

Truly the best RV park we have stayed in. The park is really clean, bathrooms are nice with spacious showers. The spaces are generously sized and there is lots of green space. I'd say my only complaint, being a dog owner, is that the dog run area is a little small and there's no grass but that truly is a minor complaint as there are plenty of areas to walk the dogs nearby. < text>
We stayed at Golden Shore RV Resort in September 2018 for 5 days.  It's located at the water front of Long Beach, CA.  The setting is nice and well kept.  It has code operated gates for security.  We used it to park our trailer as a base camp to explore attractions in LA and didn't used the pool and other facilities in the park so we couldn't comment on that.  On the last day of our stay, we actually felt sorry that we didn't book for a week as the weekly rate was only $40 more than what we paid for.  We could have more time to enjoy the surrounding area.

The RV sites are not too spacious,  a California thing I guess. It's just wide enough to park my trailer with 1 slide-out and have the tow vehicle parked besides it. The hook-ups are conveniently located at where they should be and that gets full mark.  The reason I didn't give it a 5 star was lack of WiFi as advertised in their web site.  Only a notice posted in the office counter saying WiFi was not available due to building renovation but not a word was mentioned on their web site.</text>

< Rating>

<text>Almost everything is right with Golden Shore RV Resort.  Perfect location, pretty grounds, clean facilities, friendly and helpful staff, full hookups, etc.  You can catch a free shuttle bus out front or take a healthy walk to the Shoreline Drive  or a different frer shuttle to the Queen Mary (avoid weekends).  The only issue I have (and it's an important one to me) is their dog run facilities.  It's located so far in the back and is an insult to dogs everywhere.  It's gravel, nasty looking and my dogs wouldn't even go in.  Might work for small dogs but even then rather questionable.  Almost everyone I saw took their dogs off the property to have them potty.  There are easily some better spots within the park that they could convert to a better dog friendly area.  This reason alone is the ONLY reason I gave them a 4 rather than 5 stars.  I still HIGHLY recommend this place.  Some have complained the spots are tight to back into but we have a 40 foot 5th wheel and didn't have a huge issue.< /text><pictures>None<//pictures>< resp>
None</resp>

< Review>
Well located, Golden Shores, is within walking distance to many of Long Beaches' many wonderful attractions.  The Port of Long Beach bustles with the intriguing business of world import/export and the folks of Long Beach are warm and welcoming.  All of the attractions of the Greater Los Angeles metropolis are within easy reach, as long as you don't mind the massive traffic jams....and there's no such thing as "rush hour", if people are awake, there's traffic.  So, just plan for extra time on the road and enjoy your visit.

The park itself is compact  but very well kept, in fact this is one of the best kept parks we've visited. We have seen few parks where the staff are so committed to a clean, neat and we'll groomed location.  Each pad is level and spacious; when an RV pulls out, the staff come by to clean up, water the DG and rake the site completely level again before a new family moves in. The entire park is swept and kept in perfect order daily.

There are only 2 draw - backs to this park.  The Manager is dedicated to making sure the rules are STRICTLY enforced, which can cause conflicts on occassion.  There is no allowance for consideration of special circumstances that might allow for small deviations.  For some this will not present any problems, but know that all the rules are absolutely enforced.

The park is also located in the midst of a very busy traffic pattern, so if you are looking to get away from city noise and traffic, this would not be your choice.

When you consider the park, on balance, it is a good place to stay, so when you're in a Southern California frame of mind do consider Golden Shores.  We'll be back!<//Review>

< Review>
Nice location and easy access to the best Long Beach has to offer.
There is a jogging/biking trail right next to the Resort.  The trail runs thru the local parks, the lighthouse, the Catalina Express station and the main boardwalk with all the restaurants and shops.  Perfect view of the Queen Mary and the old Sproose Goose dome.
The weather is perfect year around.
The park itself is clean, has a pool, a small convenience store, and the staff is very helpful.< /Review>

<userid>112896622898662163557</userid><GmapID>0x80dd3133882a49bb:0x4f6ad38d251241d0</GmapID></record></dataset><record>
<text>7 night stay in mid-June 2018.

Reasonably priced RV park with nice landscaping.  The sites are clean and well maintained.  Most of the sites are a hardpacked sand/dirt, there are a couple that are all concrete and a couple that are covered with artificial turf.  There is a small bark park that is also covered in artificial turf.  Community fire pit and several community tables and BBQs.  The bathrooms/showers were clean, showers were hot.  Showers are not coin operated.  There is a small store with a few items you might need and a few that you might just want (like ice cream).

Sites are FHU, with a hedge between the neighboring sites and a picnic table.  There are 4 sites that are nose in and do not have a hedge; this is nice if you are traveling with another RV and at least one is a motorhome.  The motorhome can nose in, the other can back in.  That way the entry doors face each other and there is a little courtyard between the RVs.  These site do not have a hedge.

The sites are not especially large, but are definitely adequate.  Folks with slides on both sides of their RV will find that the passenger side slides take up a fair amount of the free space at the site.  You are allowed the RV and two additional vehicles at the site as long as the additional vehicles can completely fit on the site.

Easy walk to downtown LB (WTC, Federal Building, etc.)  Easy walk to several restaurants, Catalina Express and the acquarium.

There is a bike/walk path along one side of the park (lagoon side).  One of our camp chairs was stolen from our site that bordered the bike path; I suspect that somebody on the path climbed over the fence and took it.

I witnessed the on-site staff go out of their way to assist a traveling couple from another country that ended up at the park late at night, after hours.  The park was full but they found room for them to park for the night.  It would have been easy for the staff to just say they were full and turn them away.  Kudos!

Sites are $60 weekday / $69 Fri/Sat, with a discount for a full week.  Based on the location, the condition of the park, the condition of the site, the size of the site, the overall cleanliness of the park and the kindness of the staff, and the value, I give them 5 stars.< /text>< name>
Jeff Ellis<//name>

None< /pics>

<name>Scott Rutherford< /name><time>1534859384775</time><Rate>2< /Rate><Review>Reasonably comfortable place to stay. Convenient location. Spaces are small and most are dirt/gravel, so quite dusty. As another reviewer observed, there is a significant problem with ants. Being the site is so close to the port, the air quality can also suffer somewhat from diesel fumes. But the pool area was nice and the laundry facilities were inexpensive and worked fine.

Very unhappy about the management's failure to inform us about their apparently lengthy and planned wifi outage. We made a reservation in February for a stay in August, and were expecting wifi access during our stay. We only found out upon our arrival that their wifi was down due to construction. The responsible action for management would have been a simple email to let us know in advance so we could decide whether to change our plans. Or at least a discount on the cost of the site, considering the services rendered were less than we had been told to expect. But we got neither - very dissatisfied with this aspect of our stay. We called the office about this but were told the person we needed to speak with was not available, but that "hey, the wifi is free, so what's the big deal?" Sure, the water is free too, and I'd be pretty upset if we had been given a water hookup that didn't work. Wifi, like water, is a utility that is promised as part of the cost of the site, and not providing the working service or a discount is not acceptable.<//Review><pictures>None<//pictures>< response>

But, via email, im told me there is no availability until November for the time slot so i said i could do other dates & I then asked what days do you have available? They said nothing until November. So i call and they actually had availability & a few empty spots while here.

I'm out here for family & trying to work dates. So on my part, i did not have exact timeframe. When i checked in they explained there is no refunds once paid. So i booked the firm dates & asked if i could add as needed. She said sure but no guarantee. So aporox 15 minutes i came back to add a day and she said i would have to change sites my site was now booked for the extra day. Ill take that but wow they have the same size sites empty & a few too boot but mine is not available an extra day?

Not very cordial and just makes you think, why are you in a customer service business.

In addition, im traveling alone & asked if they help you back in she said no you have to ask someone in the park. Just came frim Orangeland and they were great and insist they help you back in! Both places, Shoreline & Orangeland, said they don't assist & the other does assit respectively due to liability. Ok. So thats fine RVers are always nice and willing to help.

So for staff and reservation the park gets a 2.0 oh and also the lettter about bikes being stolen in the park, so not a safe feeling. Who wants creepers crawling.

(Translated by Google) Very good! The best I stayed in California. Highly recommend to everyone staying in LA. Very safe, pass security. Located on Long Beach, it is about 15 kilometers from Carson / LA's Cruise America RV. Excellent service, clean bathrooms, large laundry, heated pool and jacuzzi. Vacant parking lots sites with good electrical, water and sewage connections. Price + -U $ 100.00 per night. Make your reservation in advance! Ever! In all RV Resort! And I only suggest staying at RV Resort, because only in them you find safety, electricity, water and sewage and clean bathrooms, laundry, because it is jacuzzi. In them, I always recommend two nights. And in this specifically, the Golden ashore, I suggest the first and last night, as it is near to withdraw, adapt, acclimate, and at the end of the trip, return your RV on Cruise America. Attention! I never recommend sleeping on the street, or in Walmart parking yards, supermarkets, Outlets, etc. and not any other, as they are very unsafe, dangerous, walkers are everywhere and in LA and such places have no electricity. And in winter it is essential to turn on the electric heating of the RV. Never park your RV between two spaces as you will be locked. Just park it in the last two spaces, right at the end and in the corner of the parking lots, so you can safely leave the parking space. And always, always ask someone to get out of the car and help you back up and if possible take a portable reverse camera and plug it into a GPS. Beware of tree branches as they do not appear on cameras or reverse sensors, but hit the roof of the RV!

< review>
Ordered a French Vanilla Latte from here many times. Good customer service - might take longer sometimes, but that's fine as they are quite swamped with orders. I've never tried any of their food/snacking items because I only love their coffee drinks. Their lattes have a unique bean taste that I like. One time, they messed up part of my order and got me a Medium instead of a Large. They quickly fixed the error once I told them and prepared a brand new drink for me with the correct specifications - free of charge. Now, that's good customer service. Overall, I love coming to their drive thru. Highly recommend their drinks. Hardworking employees deserve credit!</review>

< Text>
An anomaly occurred today for me at this location. I went to the drive thru during operating hours and no one was there. After waiting for some time I decided I was going to leave. When I got to the pay window I saw someone behind the counter making their own drink. I gave the benefit of the doubt and figured they just arrived to work. I went to the drive thru again...15 minutes later still no service. A vehicle got behind me and I left for another coffee spot. Again, an anomaly for this particular location, but now it's reliability for me has been tarnished greatly.<//Text>

<Date>1611113563606< /Date><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
Ordered takeout Grilled pork chop, shredded pork and steam egg patty dish, and Stir fried egg noodle w/tofu and mixed vegetables, and a house milk tea with boba through DoorDash. The pickup was ready in around 20 min and easy to order.

I had the stir fried egg noodle which I loved and it is one of the best noodle I ever had. There was a lot of tofu pieces, but if someone likes saucy noodle this is not a good option.

My husband had the other dish and he too loved it. There was enough rice and the quantity of all the side dishes were really good!

For the milk tea we ordered less ice and less sugar. It was definitely less sweet and I wish there was more boba since it is an extra 50 cents.<//review>

<rate>4<//rate><Text>This place has the best best best pho broth! I usually load on the lime, basil, hoisin, and Sriracha, but because the broth was so deeply flavorful, I went au natural with my pho. (and I never do that.) I also like their water. It's infused with lemon and some herb, although if you ask the waitress, she will say it's just lemon. But we could see the pitchers from afar and there is definitely some herb in them! The menu is huge and featured several Chinese dishes as well. (They have clay pot!!) The service was nice and the place was very clean. They recently renovated and I was digging it. The only reason I didn't rate 5 stars is because the pho took an extremely long time to come out, and we had to rush through lunch (instead of enjoying it) to get back to work. We also wished there were more noodles in the bowl. Maybe that's where you would need to order the large bowl. I really liked the pho, but I'm not sure I will be able to go back during lunch breaks if it takes so long.< /Text>< pics>

< username>
airica cisneros< /username>
<Text>I'm half vietnamese so I've had a lot of vietnamese food. This is my first time coming here, and since I'm vegetarian, there isn't a lot of selection for vegetarians/vegans here in Tracy compared to the selection you get in San Jose.

I ordered V5, which is a cold noodle salad type of dish. This dish is very common among vietnamese people, and my mom makes me this all the time. I do have to say, that I was surprised how good the food was. It was much more spicier than the other variations I've tried. It seems they've combined two beloved vegetarian/vegan dishes like the lemongrass tofu and cold noodle salad into a more flavor-packed combination. I will be coming back, and am excited to try the other chay/vegan dishes they have to offer.

The downside however, is that the customer service was a bit lacking and slow. If you're the type that minds having to flag down the waiter, or in a rush, then I would say this place may not be for you.  On the positive side, this place is fairly comfortable and relaxing. It was a nice experience for me nonetheless, and a time where I could just rest and not feel rushed.< /Text><rating>4< /rating><gmapID>0x809019f201dfb8c9:0x4b703d6b780cbbc8<//gmapID><Date>1576883958255< /Date>< pictures>

Went here for the first time today and loved it. I had the s4 grilled pork B√°hn M√¨ and a vietnamese iced coffee. The sandwich was SO good and so filling. The meat had such good flavor and everything on it tasted so fresh. I would absolutely order again. The coffee was also good, super strong and sweet. < review>
Honest, amicable man. I came in for a brake inspection and possible brake pad replacement(s). The man, who I am assuming is Young, took a quick drive with the car and a quick inspection of the brakes and told me both how much brake pad I had left as well as the fact that I could probably go another 5,000 miles or so before requiring a brake pad replacement. He was also kind enough to suggest that the next time I get an oil change, I should ask them how much brake pad I have left to gauge the situation.

The quote he gave me over the phone was also super reasonable when compared to the other places I was browsing through.

I would definitely want to bring my car here when I do need to replace my brake pads!</review>

<gmap_id>0x80e84c296c460a0f:0x428db7eefaa505dd< /gmap_id><Review>I would not award them any stars.  I am very disappointed with this library.  They are not honoring their mission statement.  They are not providing free and equal access to resources or services.  I just relocated to Oxnard and I don't have access to a printer at home.  I went to the library to print out paperwork that I need to enroll my son in preschool. I took my 3 year old son in the stroller.  When I entered the computer lab I was informed that strollers were prohibited.  I was also informed that I would not be able to use the computer since their policy "printed in black and white" indicates that there is only "one person per computer" and my 3 year old son and I count as 2 people. By the way, this policy for the computer lab is not posted on their website.  It is posted by the computer lab.   I informed the attendant that my son would not be accessing the computer.  The attendant then informed me that I would have to use the computers outside the lab and that he could waive the two dollar fee.  Yes that would have been fine, but in the future when I go to the library with all of my children I will be restricted to use the computers outside of the lab and pay two dollars an hour.  This is a discriminatory practice against families.
This is incredibly disappointing.  My kids love spending time at the library.  I will not be a patron at this library or any of them in the county for that matter.  I will not allow my children to be patrons either.  I will not support an institution that has such discriminatory practices against families.

<Rating>4</Rating>< Text>
My favorite library in the local area. Friendly staff. Selection of books, periodicals, tapes, etc. seems to have gone down recently.  Still the free wi-fi, quiet, and comfortable settings makes this a nice place to read.

The Oxnard Public Library is a free public library system operated by the City of Oxnard, California. It has three locations: the Downtown Main Library, the South Oxnard Branch Library, and the Colonia Branch Library.

The main downtown library moved from the Carnegie building to a larger facility in 1963 and again in 1992. Through the mid-to-late 20th century the library also expanded its service throughout the city of Oxnard beyond the main building, first by offering bookmobile service (1956-1989) and then by opening additional branch locations. The South Oxnard Branch opened in 1989 and moved into a new facility in 2007. Colonia Branch, a small neighborhood branch adjacent to Del Sol Park, opened in 1978.</Text>

<userid>115104848618478614014</userid>< Review>
This place is almost a town center for Sky Londa, which is almost a town.  It is kind of a great cross roads and pit stop for the motorcycle enthusiasts and folk heading to the myriad parks and beaches nearby.
The place itself can be rented out for events. It is a popular place for a wedding, one of which I attended years ago.
"Next door" is gas, public bathrooms, a restaurant and a general store.
The cross roads are often full of the various types of tourist and has a nice energy.  Crowds are mostly white and Asian, but not exclusively. It has that tourist trap feel (and those prices) but everyone is welcome.<//Review>

<name>Megan Welker<//name><time>1590085557474< /time><rate>5< /rate>< review>
I've worked as a photographer at The Mountain Terrace a handful of times over the past two years and can just say that it is one of my absolute favorite venues. Every wedding is so different, but the deck keeps a really intimate backyard feel throughout the reception for friends and family to really spend quality time together. The ceremony site facing redwoods is SO beautiful and the redwood grove on site makes for some beautiful portraits at any time of day. Not to mention how incredibly sweet and thoughtful the entire staff is. I have felt so lucky to work at such a gorgeous wedding venue and look forward to working here again!!<//review>

< Review>
I have been professionally DJing weddings for over 20 years and have played many venues throughout the Bay Area. Mountain Terrace is easily my favorite place to play.  Aside from the beautiful location with breathtaking views, the staff is top notch and totally on top of their game. Their attention to detail is impeccable. Brooke and company run a tight ship, know exactly what needs to happen and how to best execute a plan of action. They ask all the right questions and make super helpful suggestions throughout the entire process. As a vendor, communication and keeping me in the loop is key to running a smooth event. I always feel confident that I will be kept abreast as to what needs to happen (announcements, music cues, special moments, etc.) well in advance so that I can be ready when the time comes.  As for the food, it is always superb and much, much better than the usual wedding caterer fare. I have played some very high-end venues whose food pales by comparison.  I cannot recommend this place highly enough. Trust your special day to the staff at Mountain Terrace. You will be in very good, capable hands for your special day.< /Review>

<Text>My boyfriend and I are currently cycling across all 48 states to set a Guinness world record. We are riding electric bikes, and when we arrived in the area we were in need of a charge. These bikes use 10 cents of electricity per charge, so 20 cents total to charge the 2 bikes. Mountain terrace was closed due to covid-19 when we arrived. We bought food and coffee from the trading post store (in the same building as mountain Terrace) and plugged our bikes into the only outlet on the building, which happened to be in front of mountain terrace. Since the business was closed, we figured they would have no issue with us charging our bikes outside of the building. About 30 minutes later we see a police officer unplug our bikes and we walk over to see what‚Äôs going on. Apparently, the owners were inside working and got very upset that we were ‚Äústealing their electricity.‚Äù We were lucky to find the restaurant across the street that allowed us to charge our bikes.. otherwise we would have been COMPLETELY STRANDED in this area due to the rude staff at mountain terrace. I cannot stress enough how unfriendly they were to us. BEWARE!</Text><pics>None< /pics><response>{'time': 1589921081513, 'text': "Wow, what an amazing thing you and your boyfriend are doing.
